neighbors.name: Milligan Energy Center LLC
neighbors.claims: Milligan Energy Center LLC is a project entity formed by Ørsted for a planned 315 MW solar farm with a 315 MW/1,260 MWh battery storage system in Eloy, Pinal County ([Milligan Energy Center](https://milliganenergycenter.com)). The project is described as a long-term asset intended to provide power to approximately 68,000 homes ([Milligan Energy Center](https://milliganenergycenter.com)). Ørsted projects that the facility will create upwards of 300 construction jobs and generate local tax revenue ([Milligan Energy Center](https://milliganenergycenter.com)). The Eloy City Council approved the project in a 5-2 vote, with representation from the Rose Law Group ([Rose Law Group Reporter](https://www.roselawgroup.com/milligan-energy-center-court-rich-rose-law-group-co-founder-and-director-of-the-firms-renewable-energy-utility-infrastructure-department-helps-secure-project-approval-in-eloy/)). Arizona Public Service (APS) has identified the need for a new 230 kV line and substation, referred to as the "Milligan" substation, to connect this project to the grid ([APS Ten-Year Plan](https://www.oasis.oati.com/woa/docs/AZPS/AZPSdocs/2025_APS_Ten-Year_Plan.pdf)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Backed by Ørsted (global energy firm); approved by City Council despite some dissenting votes; significant local infrastructure (substation) named after project.

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage Ørsted’s development manager directly; explore collaboration or land agreements that align their project with yours, highlighting mutual benefits and avoiding conflicts in grid interconnection

neighbors.name: Eloy 170 LLC
neighbors.claims: Eloy 170 LLC is an Arizona limited-liability company actively developing land in the Eloy area. The entity is pursuing a General Plan Amendment and rezoning for a project known as "Eloy Commons," which includes two sites: "Eloy Commons North" (33.86 acres) and "Eloy Commons South" (111.1 acres) located near Milligan Road and Sunshine Blvd ([AZBEX](https://azbex.com/planning-development/eloy-pz-hears-dual-requests-for-major-land-use-overhaul/)). The proposed development includes light industrial, commercial, and residential uses ([AZBEX](https://azbex.com/planning-development/eloy-pz-hears-dual-requests-for-major-land-use-overhaul/)). In June 2025, Eloy 170 LLC sold a parcel in this vicinity to Blue Beacon, Inc. (a truck wash operator), consistent with the area's industrial development focus ([ROX Commercial](https://roxcommercial.com/blog/tag/pinal-county/)). The project applicant listed for Eloy 170 LLC in city documents is LBG Development, LLC ([AZBEX](https://azbex.com/planning-development/eloy-pz-hears-dual-requests-for-major-land-use-overhaul/)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Actively engaging with City Planning and Zoning for a major master-planned development (Eloy Commons) spanning over 140 acres.

approach_recommendations.engage: Contact the LLC’s representative or LBG Development, LLC; coordinate regarding utility easements and road infrastructure as they are actively entitling adjacent land for mixed-use and industrial development.

neighbors.name: Arizona Public Service Company
neighbors.claims: Arizona Public Service Company (APS) is the state’s largest electric utility and has acquired land in this vicinity for planned grid infrastructure, specifically the Sundance to Milligan 230 kV transmission line and the Milligan substation ([APS Ten-Year Plan](https://www.oasis.oati.com/woa/docs/AZPS/AZPSdocs/2025_APS_Ten-Year_Plan.pdf)). APS exerts a major economic impact as Arizona’s top taxpayer, contributing roughly $11.3 billion annually to the state’s economy ([Pinal Post](https://pinalpost.com/pinal-county-energy-crisis-forces-push-to-solar-gas-and-battery-projects/)). The utility has publicly emphasized the need for more solar farms and battery storage in Pinal County to meet a projected 40% surge in power demand over six years ([Pinal Post](https://pinalpost.com/pinal-county-energy-crisis-forces-push-to-solar-gas-and-battery-projects/)). APS’s expansion plans in Pinal, including the new 230 kV infrastructure, indicate it is actively facilitating renewable projects to improve grid reliability and capacity ([APS Ten-Year Plan](https://www.oasis.oati.com/woa/docs/AZPS/AZPSdocs/2025_APS_Ten-Year_Plan.pdf)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Largest electric utility in region; significant taxpayer and employer; deep political and regulatory influence on local development; critical infrastructure partner.

approach_recommendations.engage: Coordinate with APS’s government affairs and transmission planning teams early; align the project’s benefits with APS’s grid needs and policy goals to secure their buy-in and support

neighbors.name: MDT Investments Ltd Pship
neighbors.claims: MDT Investments Ltd Partnership is a private landholding entity with a registered address in Phoenix, Arizona ([Homes.com](https://www.homes.com/property/2929-n-47th-ave-phoenix-az/z0z9mcv61f42r/)). The Arizona Corporation Commission database contains no active domestic corporate registration for this exact name, suggesting it may be a legacy limited partnership or registered via the Secretary of State ([ecorp.azcc.gov](https://ecorp.azcc.gov/BusinessSearch/BusinessInfo?entityNumber=01077022)). Public records link the entity to property transactions involving Malcolm D. Taylor in the mid-1990s, indicating a potential family trust or legacy ownership structure ([Homes.com](https://www.homes.com/property/2929-n-47th-ave-phoenix-az/z0z9mcv61f42r/)). No active business operations, websites, or public notices were found for the partnership in Pinal County, consistent with a passive land-holding strategy. Pinal County farmers face significant water cutbacks, a regional issue that typically makes agricultural landholders sensitive to development impacts on water resources ([Fox 10 Phoenix](https://www.fox10phoenix.com/news/some-pinal-county-farmers-facing-stark-choice-as-drought-persists)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Passive entity with no visible leadership or recent political activity in the county.

approach_recommendations.engage: Contact via the Phoenix mailing address associated with tax records; treat as a passive investor; emphasize low water usage of the proposed project compared to agriculture.

neighbors.profile_summary: Private limited partnership with legacy holdings; appears to be a passive investment vehicle with no active local footprint.

neighbors.name: Dye Equities LLC et al
neighbors.claims: Dye Equities LLC is an Arizona limited liability company associated with the Dye family, prominent in the region's industrial gas and welding supply industry (Phoenix Welding Supply) ([Phoenix Welding Supply History](https://phxwelding.com/history/)). The entity has appeared in Arizona Corporation Commission dockets related to water utility regulation, specifically filing comments in Global Water Resources cases, indicating active engagement in land-use and utility infrastructure matters ([ACC eDocket](https://edocket.azcc.gov/search/docket-search/item-detail/13404)). The LLC is also linked to equine investments, with records listing "Dye Equities and Gil Dye" as buyers in thoroughbred transactions ([Equibase](https://www.equibase.com/profiles/Results.cfm?type=Horse&refno=4469244&registry=T&rbt=TB)). While the entity itself functions as a land-holding vehicle, the principals have deep local business roots and established regulatory awareness ([Phoenix Welding Supply History](https://phxwelding.com/history/)). General regional concerns regarding water availability likely apply to their agricultural land holdings ([Fox 10 Phoenix](https://www.fox10phoenix.com/news/some-pinal-county-farmers-facing-stark-choice-as-drought-persists)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Principals are established business owners (Phoenix Welding Supply) with a history of engagement in utility regulatory dockets.

approach_recommendations.engage: Leverage the family's business background; approach with technical competence regarding utility infrastructure; acknowledge their sophistication in regulatory matters.

neighbors.name: Torino Holdings LLC
neighbors.claims: Torino Holdings LLC is an affiliate of Torino Group, Inc., a real estate development and management firm based in Carlsbad, California, with active operations in Arizona ([Torino Group About Us](https://www.torinogroupinc.com/about-us/)). The firm is led by President Cole C.P. Torino and specializes in multi-family residential development and property repositioning ([Torino Group About Us](https://www.torinogroupinc.com/about-us/)). Corporate filings link Torino Holdings LLC to the same management structure, confirming it serves as a holding vehicle for the group's real estate assets ([BizProfile](https://www.bizprofile.net/principal-address/1497-sw-martin-downs-blvd-palm-city-fl-34990)). The company explicitly lists Arizona as a key market for its construction and development activities ([Torino Group Construction](https://www.torinogroupinc.com/construction/)). Given their developer profile, their interest in the parcel is likely strategic investment or future development potential rather than long-term passive holding ([Torino Group About Us](https://www.torinogroupinc.com/about-us/)).
neighbors.influence_justification: Professional real estate developer with cross-state operations; holds significant capital resources but leadership is out-of-state.

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage directly with Cole C.P. Torino or corporate leadership; frame proposals in terms of development synergies or exit strategies; appeal to their developer mindset.

neighbors.name: New Sunshine Fund LLC
neighbors.claims: In July 2022, Walton Global sold approximately 92 acres within Eloy’s Sunshine Industrial Park (part of a larger 277-acre master plan) to an undisclosed buyer for industrial development [Walton Global — news, 2022-07-15](https://walton.com/walton-global-sells-land-in-sunshine-industrial-park/). The site was described by Walton Global executives as “prime real estate” with access to two major interstates (I-10 and I-8) and a Union Pacific rail line, intended to attract businesses and jobs to the area [Walton Global — news, 2022-07-15](https://walton.com/walton-global-sells-land-in-sunshine-industrial-park/). The purchasing company’s identity was withheld at the time of the transaction for market reasons [Walton Global — news, 2022-07-15](https://walton.com/walton-global-sells-land-in-sunshine-industrial-park/). The connection between this specific entity and the global "Sunshine Fund" investment platform could not be definitively verified in public records for Pinal County.
neighbors.influence_justification: Controls a significant strategic industrial parcel (approx. 92 acres) with rail and interstate access; originally purchased from a major land asset manager.

approach_recommendations.engage: Monitor Pinal County planning/zoning filings to identify specific development plans; engage via registered agent or property tax contact address once available.

neighbors.profile_summary: New Sunshine Fund LLC holds approximately 92 acres in the Sunshine Industrial Park, acquired from Walton Global in 2022. The site is strategically located near I-10/I-8 and Union Pacific rail lines. Detailed beneficial ownership remains opaque.

neighbors.name: State Of Arizona
neighbors.claims: The Arizona State Land Department (ASLD) actively manages State Trust Land in Pinal County and has a 'strong commitment to facilitate utility scale solar energy projects' ([source](https://land.az.gov/solar-applications)) Leased land for the 300MW Box Canyon Solar Project near Florence, which began operations in 2025 ([source](https://brightnightpower.com/what-we-do/our-projects/box-canyon/)) The Box Canyon project is expected to generate over $65 million in land lease payments to the State Land Trust over its lifetime ([source](https://www.power-technology.com/news/box-canyon-solar-project-operation/)) Processing application for the Silver King Solar project, which proposes to redesignate 8,891 acres of State Trust Land for energy production ([source](https://pinalpost.com/countys-largest-solar-farm-proposal-highlights-rush-of-renewable-energy-applications/))
neighbors.influence_justification: Major landowner and regulatory authority for solar leases.

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage via Arizona State Land Department commercial leasing process.

Their primary motivation is revenue generation for State Trust beneficiaries (schools, hospitals).

overview_summary: Screening of 12 neighbors within 0.5 miles identified one resident and 11 organizational entities, including institutional investors, renewable energy developers, and a major regional utility. While eight neighbors maintain an unknown stance, four have expressed support and none have voiced opposition. High-influence stakeholders include Arizona Public Service (APS) and Ørsted’s Milligan Energy Center, both of which signal corporate-backed support for regional energy infrastructure. The remaining neighbors are primarily speculative landholders and investment-focused LLCs, with research identifying potential risks related to farming interests and water preservation.
